CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 2, 1959, pg. 13, reads: "Love's Labor's Lost...Sometimes Home is Where the Heart Remains - Former House Site - Percy Golden, the popular Hill District barber, used to own a house where there is nothing but foundation and rubbish not at Kirkpatrick and Rose Sts."
TitMainTitle: Vacant lot on corner of street with houses on either side, including one on right with brick asphalt siding, Kirkpatrick and Rose Streets, Hill District
